UNITED STATES, ex rel. Lukas PSARELIS, Appellant, v. W. H. MARSHALL, District Director of Immigration. No. 4759. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. June 28, 1932. Ward Bonsall, of Pittsburgh, Pa., for appellant. Louis E. Graham, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Lloyd W. Bryan, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Pittsburgh, Pa., for appellee.

Before BUEEINGTON, WOOLLEY, and THOMPSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This case is similar in its facts to Philip-pides v. Day, 283 U. S. 48, 51 S. Ct. 358, 75 L. Ed. 833. It is affirmed on that ease.
